17:21.160 --> 17:24.040
<i>And Buster realized
he may havejust scared away a man...</i>

17:24.160 --> 17:27.960
<i>who supported him in the way
he'd always hoped his own father would.</i>

17:35.760 --> 17:37.320
<i>And Michael headed
over to the mall.</i>

17:37.440 --> 17:38.565
- So what the hell is this?

17:38.600 --> 17:40.960
- Hey, Dad, I didn't know
we were shoplifting, okay?

17:41.080 --> 17:43.480
Shoplifting?
What's the matter with you, Gob?

17:43.600 --> 17:45.760
What's the matter with me?
She's the shoplifter!

17:45.880 --> 17:48.560
- I wasn't shoplifting, you twit.
- Yes, thanks to me.

17:48.640 --> 17:50.880
No. I work here.

17:51.000 --> 17:51.800
At least I used to.

17:51.800 --> 17:54.800
They fired me because they thought
I was helping this idiot shoplift.

17:54.880 --> 17:57.480
Also, they said I wasn't
a very good salesgirl.

17:57.600 --> 18:00.520
You can't be serious?

18:00.640 --> 18:02.520
<i>A salesgirl.</i>

18:02.640 --> 18:04.800
I knew it! I knew you
couldn't pull it off.

18:04.880 --> 18:07.640
There's only one magician
in this family and that is me.

18:07.720 --> 18:10.560
And you got caught by a 13-year-old girl.

18:10.680 --> 18:13.600
You know, this is why I'm constantly
asking you to stay away from my son.

18:13.720 --> 18:15.640
Yeah, well, it's not like you were there
to spend any time with me, Dad.

18:15.760 --> 18:17.600
Because I'm not daughter
enough for you.

18:17.720 --> 18:22.160
George Michael, um,
I'm always there for you, okay?

18:22.240 --> 18:23.800
It's just you're getting
a little too manly

18:23.835 --> 18:25.080
for Bring Your Daughter to Work Day.

18:25.160 --> 18:26.725
- Dad, that's what makes it funny.

18:26.760 --> 18:29.760
- I also wanted to give Maeby
a good role model for a change.

18:29.840 --> 18:33.440
Yeah, well, I guess, you looking out for
her is probably something she could use.

18:33.520 --> 18:35.520
Where is Maeby?

18:35.640 --> 18:38.160
<i>Michael realized he had
to get to the police station...</i>

18:38.240 --> 18:42.200
<i>before they got ahold of Maeby, to whom
he'd promised $50 to tell the truth.</i>

18:42.320 --> 18:44.280
I've put a bounty on my own head.

18:44.360 --> 18:48.280
<i>But Maeby's instincts to lie returned.</i>

18:48.360 --> 18:50.200
Hey, you can't go in there.

18:50.280 --> 18:52.840
No, it's okay.
I'm Detective Fellows's daughter.

18:52.960 --> 18:56.920
Oh. Oh, sorry. It's four-three-five.
And that opens any door in the building.

18:57.040 --> 18:58.920
Great. Thanks.

19:04.640 --> 19:08.120
<i>And it was there that Maeby
discovered the key to Michael's freedom.</i>

19:08.200 --> 19:10.040
Well, I appreciate your honesty.

19:10.120 --> 19:12.440
Maeby. What-What-What'd she say?

19:12.520 --> 19:15.000
I said there's a tape of Kitty getting
on the boat and that you guys blew it up.

19:15.080 --> 19:17.760
I told them the truth,
like you told me.

19:17.840 --> 19:19.840
That-a-girl.

19:19.960 --> 19:21.800
That's right. That's,
uh, that's the truth.

19:21.835 --> 19:23.160
That's everything that we know.

19:24.640 --> 19:26.520
You're free to go.

19:29.320 --> 19:31.480
Great. Here we go.

19:35.320 --> 19:37.960
- What the hell just happened?
- Relax. They got nothing on you.

19:38.080 --> 19:40.680
They're bluffing. Kitty's alive.
I just saw her in the back room.

19:40.800 --> 19:43.600
They just wanted to get you scared,
so you'd testify against Pop-Pop.

19:44.720 --> 19:46.640
Unbelievable. Oh, that's great.

19:46.720 --> 19:49.240
You just told them the truth;
they let us walk.

19:49.360 --> 19:52.560
- I guess I owe you 50 bucks, huh?
- Yeah. I'd save your money.

19:52.640 --> 19:55.600
Kitty's got a lot of evidence,
and she thinks that you tried to kill her.

19:55.680 --> 19:57.840
So you're probably going to
need a better attorney.

20:00.640 --> 20:03.400
<i>Lo siento.</i>

20:03.520 --> 20:06.680
I hate Bring Your Daughter to Work Day.

20:06.760 --> 20:09.400
<i>On the next
Arrested Development.</i>

20:09.480 --> 20:14.000
<i>Tobias loses his securityjob
trying to solve the store's mice problem.</i>

20:14.080 --> 20:19.200
<i>Lindsay, now without a job,
goes with her initial instinct.</i>

20:19.280 --> 20:21.120
Mom, we're gonna
be late for practice!

20:21.200 --> 20:24.040
<i>- And Annyong exacts his revenge.
- Where is everybody?</i>

